|  | For the Years Ended December 31, |  | 
--- | --- | --- | --- | ---
 | 2019 | 2018 | Increase/ (decrease) | % Change
Net revenues by distribution channel: |  |  |  | 
Digital online channels (1) | $4,932 | $5,786 | $(854) | (15)%
Retail channels | 909 | 1,107 | (198) | (18)
Other (2) | 648 | 607 | 41 | 7
Total consolidated net revenues | $6,489 | $7,500 | $(1,011) | (13)

paragraph 1: Consolidated Results
paragraph 2: Net Revenues by Distribution Channel
paragraph 3: The following table details our consolidated net revenues by distribution channel (amounts in millions):
paragraph 4: (1) Net revenues from “Digital online channels” include revenues from digitally-distributed subscriptions, downloadable content, microtransactions, and products, as well as licensing royalties.
paragraph 5: (2) Net revenues from “Other” primarily includes revenues from our Distribution business and the Overwatch League.
paragraph 6: Digital Online Channel Net Revenues The decrease in net revenues from digital online channels for 2019, as compared to 2018, was primarily due to: • lower revenues recognized from the Destiny franchise (reflecting our sale of the publishing rights for Destiny to Bungie in December 2018); and • lower revenues recognized from Hearthstone.
paragraph 7: Retail Channel Net Revenues The decrease in net revenues from retail channels for 2019, as compared to 2018, was primarily due to: • lower revenues recognized from Call of Duty: Black Ops 4, which was released in October 2018, as compared to Call of Duty: WWII, which was released in November 2017; • lower revenues recognized from the Destiny franchise; and • lower revenues from Crash Bandicoot™ N. Sane Trilogy, which was released on the Xbox One, PC, and Nintendo Switch in June 2018.
paragraph 8: The decrease was partially offset by: • revenues recognized from Crash Team Racing Nitro-Fueled, which was released in June 2019; • revenues from Sekiro: Shadows Die Twice, which was released in March 2019; and • higher revenues recognized from Call of Duty: Modern Warfare, which was released in October 2019, as compared to Call of Duty: Black Ops 4.
